issue.title: Add Flashcard Generation Feature
issue.body:
Description:
Enhance Smriti AI by introducing an AI-powered flashcard generation feature that creates Anki-style flashcards from uploaded PDFs, text notes, or YouTube linked video. This will complement the existing quiz system and improve knowledge retention through spaced repetition.

Why:
-Flashcards are a proven tool for improving memory retention.
-Automating the process saves learners time and ensures important information is highlighted.
-Extends the learning workflow from content ingestion  summarization  practice  review.

Proposed Solution:
Flashcards should be with the AI Summarizies, Mind Map and Road Map feature.

-Flashcard Formatting:
-Automatically create cards in Term  Definition format.

Deck Management:
-Store cards in an in-app deck for organized review.
-Enable spaced repetition scheduling for optimal recall.

Export Options:
-Support download in Anki .apkg format and .txt format for offline use.

Acceptance Criteria:
- User can generate flashcards from PDFs, notes, or YouTube linked video.
- Flashcards are editable before saving.
- Works on both desktop and mobile versions of Smriti AI.

hostname-setup: do not trigger assertion when uname() is prohibited by seccomp

gethostname_full() is used in nss-myhostname, and hence random
application may indirectly call it. When an application with a too strict
seccomp filter loads the nss module, the application may trigger the
assertion.

Partially fixes #38582.

assert-util: drop message argument of assert_log()

As it is always equals to #expr.

assert-util: introduce log_set_assert_return_is_critical_from_env()

It will be used for testing nss modules.

nss: move definition of NSS_ENTRYPOINT_BEGIN to nss-util.h

Then, also make nss modules parse $SYSTEMD_ASSERT_RETURN_IS_CRITICAL
environment variable.

This also moves nss-util.c and nss-util.h from src/basic/ to src/shared/,
as they are not used by libsystemd.

signal-util: do not abort when sigprocmask() failed

BLOCK_SIGNALS() is also used in nss modules. If an application is
running with a too strict seccomp loads our nss modules, then the
assertion may be triggered.

Fixes #38582.
test-nss-hosts: add test case for issue #38582

Avoid triggering assertions by nss modules when uname and/or sigprocmask are masked (#38586)

Fixes #38582.

core/service: do not reset watchdong when unit is frozen

Even watchdog for a service is stopped when freezing the unit is
requested, sd-notify message WATCHDOG=1 or friends may come after
that due to ordering of event priority. In that case,
service_reset_watchdog() is called for frozen unit and thus previously
watchdog was reenabled.

Follow-up for 25178aadb2bd04ef9e63f48c1ef42fb309f9332e.
Fixes #38551 (the second failure case).

Follow-up for 5e4115e59e25fc2eeb31c8f47c3ce1b59835f215.

modules-load: implement parallel module loading

Load modules in parallel using a pool of worker threads. The number of
threads is equal to the number of CPUs, with a maximum of 16 (to avoid
too many threads being started during boot on systems with many an high
core count, since the number of modules loaded on boot is usually on
the small side).

The number of threads can optionally be specified manually using the
SYSTEMD_MODULES_LOAD_NUM_THREADS environment variable; in this case,
no limit is enforced.

issue.body:
This pull request introduces a major refactoring of the codebase to a component-based architecture, along with new features and several bug fixes.

Key changes include:

**Features:**
- Implement real-time settings and snapshot management:
    - Settings now save on input change with debouncing for performance.
    - New settings snapshot feature to automatically save up to 10 previous versions.
    - Improved "Cancel" button in settings to revert unsaved changes with confirmation.
- Inline Chat Room Renaming: 
    - Implemented inline editing for chat room names 
    - Includes a confirm button for explicit save and hides non-essential UI elements during rename.

**Refactoring:**
- Decompose index.js into a component-based structure:
    - UI rendering logic extracted into `src/components/`.
    - New `src/ui.js` for component rendering orchestration.
    - Event handling moved to `src/handlers/`.
    - Utilities separated into `api.js`, `storage.js`, `utils.js`.
- Pass prompts explicitly to API calls and add transparent favicons.
- Refactored API calls to use an options object for improved clarity and maintainability.
- Improved error handling and code readability in storage and utility functions.
- Used handler mapping for `handleModalInput`.

**Bug Fixes:**
- Apply font scale on page load.
- Correct errors in random first talk feature.
- Prevent message input loss on new character addition.
- Correct backup and restore logic in storage:
    - `handleBackup` now sources data from live application state to prevent data loss.
    - `handleRestore` now correctly restores `chatRooms` and `userStickers` with fallback defaults.
- Fix issues identified during refactoring:
    - UI rendering on initial load.
    - Removed call to non-existent `addKeyboardListeners`.
- Fixed a critical bug where chat room name changes were not persisted due to incorrect state mutation.
- Resolved an issue where the inline editing UI for chat rooms would not appear correctly.
- Fixed a bug causing the chat room deletion modal to remain open after completion.
- Addressed issues with character edit/delete modals not appearing immediately, ensuring correct state change detection. 
    - Prevented settings modal from resetting/collapsing during auto-save by moving snapshot creation to an explicit save action. 
    - Fixed character deletion confirmation modal not closing.
- Added a 500ms debounce to settings inputs to prevent UI lag and excessive re-rendering.
- Corrected event handling for character edit and delete buttons in the sidebar.
- Changed `checkStorageSpace` warning limit (renamed to `getLocalStorageFallbackUsage`).
- Applied fixes based on PR review.
